                            <div class="container">
                    <div class="exc-container">
                        <div class="muscle-text bd-bot exercise-list-start">
                            <h3><b>Lateral Deltoid</b></h3><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537056/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">lateral deltoid</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, also known as the middle deltoid, is located on the outside of the shoulder. It sits between the anterior and posterior deltoid. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Its main function is shoulder abduction, which is the movement of the arm away from the body.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">During a barbell upright row, the lateral deltoids do the heavy lifting, helping to bring the elbows up and out. This makes the barbell upright row an excellent exercise for increasing the strength and muscle size of the lateral deltoid.</span></p>                        </div>
                    </div>
